interesting_discoveries.question: Q4
interesting_discoveries.detected_name: Reading multiple inputs on one line
interesting_discoveries.detected_description: The student attempts to read two double values (e.g., x1 and y1) from a single user input prompt '(x1, y1):' by calling input.nextDouble() twice on the same line. This will force the user to enter two numbers separated by a space or new line for each prompt, which contradicts the sample run where '00' is treated as two separate inputs '0' and '0'.
